South Africa’s Rand Weakens by 0.6% Against Dollar in Johannesburg Trading

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-08-08T05:27:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/south-africa-s-rand-weakens-by-0-6-against-dollar-in-johannesburg-trading.html
South Africa ’s rand weakened 0.6
percent against the dollar in early trading in Johannesburg.  The currency of  Africa ’s largest economy declined to 6.9675
per dollar as of 7:25 a.m. local time, compared with 6.9246 late
on Aug. 5, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
